  "body": "## ðŸŽ‰ Description\r\n```\r\ncontract StandardToken is ERC20 {\r\n  mapping(address => uint256) balances;\r\n  mapping (address => mapping (address => uint256)) internal allowed;\r\n  uint256 totalSupply_;\r\n  ...\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI think that it would be best to:\r\n1. Explicitly declare the visibility of `balances` and `totalSupply_`\r\n2. Change this visibility from (implicit) `public` to `internal` (since an explicit Getter function is implemented for each one of these variables)\r\n\r\nSide note:\r\nThe 3 state variables in this contract are not conforming to the same coding convention (though I suppose that it would be a breaking change to fix it at this point).",
